{
  "_comment": [
    "AI-RSE GateOps — Version-Aware Quality Gate Policy",
    "",
    "Quality gates are NOT eternal prohibitions.",
    "They are versioned policies per development stage.",
    "",
    "In v0.3, Poisson and rho_eff are forbidden in code.",
    "In a future v0.4, they may be permitted, provided:",
    "  1. A dedicated ADR is accepted;",
    "  2. This policy is updated via PR;",
    "  3. Authorized modules are defined;",
    "  4. Mandatory tests and docs exist;",
    "  5. Implementation remains demonstrative unless curated.",
    "",
    "Quality gate does not prevent evolution;",
    "it prevents evolution out of order."
  ],

  "current_stage": "v0.3",

